1
00:00:01,546 --> 00:00:03,481
[music playing]

2
00:00:16,930 --> 00:00:17,598
-Iruka, Sensei?

3
00:00:17,632 --> 00:00:18,533
-Hmm?

4
00:00:18,566 --> 00:00:20,469
{\an1}-Tell me, did you hear the news?

5
00:00:20,502 --> 00:00:22,237
-Hear what news?

6
00:00:22,271 --> 00:00:23,939
{\an1}-Apparently last night
there was a battle

7
00:00:23,972 --> 00:00:25,741
{\an1}in the forest in the back hills.

8
00:00:25,774 --> 00:00:27,075
{\an1}-And what happened?

9
00:00:27,109 --> 00:00:30,380
{\an1}-Well, the rumor is that enemy
spies were discovered out

10
00:00:30,413 --> 00:00:31,482
there.

11
00:00:31,515 --> 00:00:33,350
{\an1}A patrol unit was able
to kill one of them

12
00:00:33,384 --> 00:00:35,553
{\an1}and bring the body back here.

13
00:00:35,586 --> 00:00:37,721
{\an1}-If that's the case, we
should warn the students

14
00:00:37,755 --> 00:00:39,958
{\an1}that they shouldn't go
near the back hills today.

15
00:00:39,991 --> 00:00:41,259
{\an1}-That's a good idea.

16
00:00:41,293 --> 00:00:43,429
{\an1}There might still be
more spies out there.

17
00:00:49,436 --> 00:00:51,738
{\an1}IRUKA (VOICEOVER): I hope
nothing's happened to him.

18
00:00:56,477 --> 00:00:58,414
{\an1}-All right, I got
to find that corpse.

19
00:00:58,447 --> 00:01:00,082
{\an1}I wonder where it could be.

20
00:01:00,115 --> 00:01:01,984
I've played here
so many times, I

21
00:01:02,017 --> 00:01:03,687
{\an1}know the place like
the back of my hand.

22
00:01:03,719 --> 00:01:07,123
{\an1}But I should have asked the guys
exactly where I should look.

23
00:01:07,157 --> 00:01:07,625
-Naruto?

24
00:01:07,658 --> 00:01:08,693
-Huh?

25
00:01:08,725 --> 00:01:10,827
-Sensei?

26
00:01:10,860 --> 00:01:13,898
{\an1}-Come on, you have to get
back to the academy now.

27
00:01:13,931 --> 00:01:14,999
-No!

28
00:01:15,032 --> 00:01:17,669
{\an1}I don't want to go to
The Academy anymore!

29
00:01:17,704 --> 00:01:18,804
{\an1}-You don't understand.

30
00:01:18,837 --> 00:01:20,872
{\an1}There are still dangerous
enemies out here.

31
00:01:20,906 --> 00:01:23,243
-I won't go back
even if you beg me!

32
00:01:23,276 --> 00:01:24,844
{\an1}-Just do as I say.

33
00:01:24,877 --> 00:01:26,879
{\an1}I'm your homeroom
teacher Naruto.

34
00:01:26,913 --> 00:01:28,515
-Oh, shut up!

35
00:01:28,549 --> 00:01:31,118
{\an1}You only act like a teacher
when it's convenient for you.

36
00:01:34,756 --> 00:01:35,991
{\an1}You don't get it.

37
00:01:36,024 --> 00:01:38,628
{\an1}You don't know what I
go through every day.

38
00:01:38,661 --> 00:01:40,096
And none of that
is going to change

39
00:01:40,129 --> 00:01:42,898
{\an1}just because I go
back to school.

40
00:01:42,932 --> 00:01:45,769
{\an1}I'm always alone.

41
00:01:45,802 --> 00:01:48,539
{\an1}I'm always left out.

42
00:01:48,573 --> 00:01:49,374
{\an1}Look, don't you see?

43
00:01:49,407 --> 00:01:50,643
{\an1}Nobody wants me around.

44
00:01:50,676 --> 00:01:52,444
Nobody cares!

45
00:01:52,478 --> 00:01:53,412
-I--

46
00:01:53,445 --> 00:01:56,048
-But this time
it'll be different.

47
00:01:56,081 --> 00:01:57,816
{\an1}If I bring something
back from out here,

48
00:01:57,850 --> 00:01:59,753
{\an1}then I'm finally going
to have some friends who

49
00:01:59,785 --> 00:02:00,787
will accept me.

50
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:03,357
{\an1}If I do that I won't
be alone anymore.

51
00:02:03,391 --> 00:02:05,326
{\an1}And I won't feel like
an outsider anymore.

52
00:02:10,565 --> 00:02:12,200
{\an1}That's why I'm going
to stay out here

53
00:02:12,234 --> 00:02:16,973
{\an1}until I can find something
good to bring back.

54
00:02:17,006 --> 00:02:17,940
-Please listen.

55
00:02:17,974 --> 00:02:19,343
I know that you
have your reasons.

56
00:02:19,376 --> 00:02:21,979
{\an1}But as your teacher, I
can't just walk away.

57
00:02:22,012 --> 00:02:25,283
{\an1}I won't allow you to stay
in such a dangerous area.

58
00:02:25,317 --> 00:02:27,586
{\an1}-You can't even try to
understand my feelings.

59
00:02:30,389 --> 00:02:32,124
{\an1}Well then, Sexy Jutsu!

60
00:02:35,796 --> 00:02:36,663
[moans]

61
00:02:36,697 --> 00:02:40,568
[screaming]

62
00:02:40,601 --> 00:02:41,202
-Ha.

63
00:02:41,235 --> 00:02:42,103
-Huh?

64
00:02:42,136 --> 00:02:43,104
No, wait!

65
00:02:43,137 --> 00:02:45,106
{\an1}-Ha, grown ups are
so easy to trick.

66
00:02:45,139 --> 00:02:46,040
{\an1}It's not even funny.

67
00:02:49,813 --> 00:02:51,247
Huh?

68
00:02:51,281 --> 00:02:55,118
{\an1}These are signs of a fight.

69
00:02:55,151 --> 00:02:56,387
{\an1}That means it's close.

70
00:03:02,327 --> 00:03:04,563
[grunting]

71
00:03:04,596 --> 00:03:05,063
Ah!

72
00:03:07,866 --> 00:03:09,837
It's not here.

73
00:03:09,869 --> 00:03:11,904
[stomach growls]

74
00:03:11,938 --> 00:03:16,110
{\an1}-Come of think of it, I haven't
eaten anything at all today.

75
00:03:16,143 --> 00:03:18,413
Maybe I can find
something out here.

76
00:03:18,446 --> 00:03:18,912
Aha!

77
00:03:21,517 --> 00:03:25,121
{\an1}Well, it looks like I
just found my lunch.

78
00:03:25,154 --> 00:03:26,288
Huh?

79
00:03:26,322 --> 00:03:26,889
What's that?

80
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:34,832
{\an1}Whoa, I've never seen a kunai
shaped like this before.

81
00:03:34,866 --> 00:03:38,202
[laughing]

82
00:03:38,236 --> 00:03:40,172
The enemy ninja
must've used this kunai

83
00:03:40,205 --> 00:03:42,642
{\an1}during the battle yesterday.

84
00:03:42,675 --> 00:03:44,910
{\an1}I found something that I can
bring back to my friends.

85
00:03:47,447 --> 00:03:51,853
{\an1}-That kunai, it has the secret
documents we're looking for.

86
00:03:51,887 --> 00:03:53,254
I see.

87
00:03:53,287 --> 00:03:56,258
{\an1}She must have placed it in that
nest before she was defeated.

88
00:03:56,291 --> 00:03:58,694
-All right!

89
00:03:58,728 --> 00:03:59,662
{\an1}-Don't let him escape.

90
00:04:03,566 --> 00:04:04,934
{\an1}-Where did he go?

91
00:04:04,967 --> 00:04:07,204
I hope he's OK.

92
00:04:07,237 --> 00:04:09,808
{\an1}-Well, he sure is a handful.

93
00:04:09,841 --> 00:04:11,309
{\an1}Listen, take my advice.

94
00:04:11,342 --> 00:04:13,411
{\an1}Don't give him any more
attention than you have to

95
00:04:13,445 --> 00:04:15,079
{\an1}and you should be fine.

96
00:04:15,113 --> 00:04:16,615
{\an1}-Leave him alone?

97
00:04:16,649 --> 00:04:19,853
Just ignore him?

98
00:04:19,886 --> 00:04:21,721
Naruto's right.

99
00:04:21,755 --> 00:04:24,024
{\an1}I've never really made an
effort to understand him

100
00:04:24,057 --> 00:04:25,392
{\an1}or what he might be feeling.

101
00:04:28,262 --> 00:04:30,666
{\an1}After the death of my
parents, there was no one

102
00:04:30,699 --> 00:04:34,002
{\an1}left to care for me or give
me the support that I needed.

103
00:04:55,595 --> 00:04:57,798
{\an1}I did a lot of stupid
things in class.

104
00:05:00,367 --> 00:05:01,803
I wanted to get
people's attention.

105
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:11,747
{\an1}Naruto, he's just
like I was back then.

106
00:05:11,781 --> 00:05:13,717
[theme music]

107
00:06:41,554 --> 00:06:43,522
[music playing]

108
00:06:56,105 --> 00:07:00,610
{\an1}-Hmm, hey Shikamaru, can I
borrow some money from you?

109
00:07:00,644 --> 00:07:02,113
{\an1}-Come on, not again.

110
00:07:02,145 --> 00:07:04,314
{\an1}Don't tell me you're spending
all of your allowance

111
00:07:04,347 --> 00:07:05,650
only on snacks?

112
00:07:05,683 --> 00:07:06,651
-Huh?

113
00:07:06,684 --> 00:07:08,086
{\an1}Shikamaru, snacks
are the only thing

114
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,721
{\an1}in the world worth
spending money on.

115
00:07:12,424 --> 00:07:13,525
-Oh, all right.

116
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:16,896
{\an1}If that's how you feel,
I'll lend you the money.

117
00:07:16,929 --> 00:07:18,531
-Hey, you two.

118
00:07:18,564 --> 00:07:19,033
-Huh?

119
00:07:19,066 --> 00:07:20,000
-Huh?

120
00:07:20,034 --> 00:07:21,135
{\an1}-Aren't you supposed
to be in school?

121
00:07:21,167 --> 00:07:22,536
-Who are you?

122
00:07:22,569 --> 00:07:24,571
{\an1}I'm not supposed to
talk to strangers.

123
00:07:24,605 --> 00:07:27,475
Otherwise my dad
will get mad at me.

124
00:07:27,509 --> 00:07:31,714
{\an1}-Well, you must be Shikamaru
Nara and Choji Akimichi.

125
00:07:31,747 --> 00:07:34,250
{\an1}-Hold on a minute,
how do know our names?

126
00:07:34,283 --> 00:07:36,285
{\an1}-You both look just
like your fathers.

127
00:07:36,318 --> 00:07:38,889
{\an1}You're Shikaku and
Choja's sons right?

128
00:07:38,922 --> 00:07:42,426
{\an1}Perhaps I should tell them
you've been skipping class.

129
00:07:42,459 --> 00:07:44,162
{\an1}-You're going to tell our dads?

130
00:07:44,195 --> 00:07:48,067
{\an1}But we both have a free period
right now, right Shikamaru?

131
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:49,601
-Why is that?

132
00:07:49,635 --> 00:07:50,769
{\an1}-It's because of Naruto.

133
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:53,305
{\an1}He went to look for a
corpse in the back heels.

134
00:07:53,338 --> 00:07:56,476
{\an1}Iruka Sensei had to
leave class to find him.

135
00:07:56,509 --> 00:07:58,713
{\an1}-Iruka Sensei went after Naruto?

136
00:07:58,746 --> 00:07:59,847
Is that true?

137
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:03,317
{\an1}-Yeah, I'm positive.

138
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,287
{\an1}-Listen, having a
free period doesn't

139
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:06,822
{\an1}mean you get to leave school.

140
00:08:06,855 --> 00:08:08,624
Go back to the
Academy right now.

141
00:08:08,658 --> 00:08:10,293
-OK.

142
00:08:10,326 --> 00:08:10,760
Uh.

143
00:08:18,036 --> 00:08:21,906
{\an1}-Now I'll be able to
make some real friends.

144
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:22,874
Huh?

145
00:08:22,907 --> 00:08:24,210
-Hey, kid.

146
00:08:24,242 --> 00:08:26,145
{\an1}-Oh great, what do you want?

147
00:08:26,178 --> 00:08:27,079
I'm in a hurry.

148
00:08:27,113 --> 00:08:30,050
{\an1}Had over that kunai
nice and easy.

149
00:08:30,083 --> 00:08:30,984
-Hmm?

150
00:08:31,017 --> 00:08:31,752
No, forget it!

151
00:08:31,785 --> 00:08:32,519
This is mine!

152
00:08:32,552 --> 00:08:34,055
{\an1}I'm not giving it to you!

153
00:08:34,088 --> 00:08:35,590
-I see.

154
00:08:35,623 --> 00:08:37,892
{\an1}Well then, we'll just
have to take it by force.

155
00:08:37,925 --> 00:08:38,526
-What?

156
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:40,996
{\an1}Just wait a second.

157
00:08:41,029 --> 00:08:42,464
[gulps]

158
00:08:42,498 --> 00:08:44,934
{\an1}[screaming in distance]

159
00:08:44,968 --> 00:08:47,370
-Naruto.

160
00:08:47,403 --> 00:08:49,305
[yelling]

161
00:08:49,339 --> 00:08:52,743
-Sexy Jutsu!

162
00:08:52,777 --> 00:08:54,678
Ooh.

163
00:08:54,712 --> 00:08:56,447
Ah!

164
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:59,918
{\an1}-Too bad that technique
won't work on us.

165
00:08:59,951 --> 00:09:02,955
Huh?

166
00:09:02,989 --> 00:09:04,457
No way!

167
00:09:04,490 --> 00:09:06,459
{\an1}You're all women?!

168
00:09:06,492 --> 00:09:06,960
Ah!

169
00:09:06,994 --> 00:09:09,163
No fair!

170
00:09:09,196 --> 00:09:11,365
{\an1}In that case, Clone Jutsu!

171
00:09:18,507 --> 00:09:21,077
{\an1}-Unbelievable That's got to
be the most pathetic excuse

172
00:09:21,111 --> 00:09:24,681
{\an1}for a clone I've ever seen.

173
00:09:24,714 --> 00:09:26,016
{\an1}Now go and get him.

174
00:09:26,049 --> 00:09:26,650
No mercy!

175
00:09:31,190 --> 00:09:33,959
[screaming]

176
00:09:33,992 --> 00:09:37,763
{\an1}-If Ninjutsu won't work
don't let them get away.

177
00:09:42,068 --> 00:09:43,603
{\an1}There are traps all
over this forest

178
00:09:43,636 --> 00:09:47,142
{\an1}and I know exactly
where they're hidden.

179
00:09:47,175 --> 00:09:48,276
-Hurry.

180
00:09:48,310 --> 00:09:49,244
-Here they come.

181
00:09:53,182 --> 00:09:54,616
[laughter]

182
00:09:54,649 --> 00:09:56,552
[grunting]

183
00:09:56,586 --> 00:09:59,455
{\an1}-Ugh, how'd we get caught
in such a simple trap?

184
00:09:59,488 --> 00:10:01,225
{\an1}That brat is mine.

185
00:10:04,095 --> 00:10:05,029
-Got to hold on.

186
00:10:05,063 --> 00:10:06,463
{\an1}I know there's another trap.

187
00:10:06,497 --> 00:10:07,298
IRUKA: Naruto!

188
00:10:07,332 --> 00:10:08,200
-Huh?

189
00:10:08,234 --> 00:10:09,667
Sensei?

190
00:10:09,701 --> 00:10:13,072
{\an1}I'm over here Sensei!

191
00:10:13,105 --> 00:10:17,510
[screaming]

192
00:10:20,948 --> 00:10:23,417
-Ah!

193
00:10:23,451 --> 00:10:24,685
[groans]

194
00:10:24,719 --> 00:10:25,320
-Hey!

195
00:10:25,354 --> 00:10:27,256
{\an1}Are you all right?

196
00:10:27,289 --> 00:10:28,891
{\an1}Come on, wake up.

197
00:10:28,924 --> 00:10:29,558
Wake up.

198
00:10:32,762 --> 00:10:34,130
-Huh?

199
00:10:34,163 --> 00:10:37,835
{\an1}-Good, at least you're awake.

200
00:10:37,868 --> 00:10:39,136
-Sensei?

201
00:10:39,169 --> 00:10:43,575
{\an1}-All right now, we have to
get you back to the academy.

202
00:10:43,608 --> 00:10:44,876
-It's them.

203
00:10:44,910 --> 00:10:46,312
{\an1}-You're not from here.

204
00:10:46,345 --> 00:10:49,015
{\an1}What are you up to sneaking
around The Leaf Village?

205
00:10:49,048 --> 00:10:51,851
{\an1}-Hmm, and just who're you?

206
00:10:51,884 --> 00:10:53,820
{\an1}Leave the kid with
us and get lost.

207
00:10:53,854 --> 00:10:56,156
I'm in charge of
this child's safety.

208
00:10:56,190 --> 00:10:57,859
{\an1}He's going home with me.

209
00:10:57,892 --> 00:10:59,727
{\an1}-What are you, his teacher?

210
00:10:59,761 --> 00:11:02,463
{\an1}-Ha, you're unfortunate to
have such a lame student.

211
00:11:02,497 --> 00:11:05,567
{\an1}Now you'll pay for his
stupidity with your life.

212
00:11:05,601 --> 00:11:08,171
{\an1}-Difficult children are
just more rewarding.

213
00:11:08,204 --> 00:11:12,075
{\an1}Besides, you won't be able
to defeat me that easily.

214
00:11:12,108 --> 00:11:14,511
{\an1}Naruto-- hang in there.

215
00:11:30,164 --> 00:11:31,464
{\an1}-Quickly, surround them!

216
00:11:35,636 --> 00:11:37,105
-Die!

217
00:11:37,138 --> 00:11:39,208
{\an1}-I will not let you hurt Naruto.

218
00:11:42,611 --> 00:11:45,048
[grunting]

219
00:11:45,082 --> 00:11:46,984
{\an1}-Don't let them escape.

220
00:11:47,017 --> 00:11:48,518
Scatter.

221
00:11:48,552 --> 00:11:49,987
{\an1}Multi Phantom Shuriken Jutsu!

222
00:11:57,963 --> 00:11:59,264
{\an1}Can't dodge them.

223
00:12:05,538 --> 00:12:07,741
What?

224
00:12:07,775 --> 00:12:11,213
{\an1}-Hey, you two all right?

225
00:12:11,246 --> 00:12:13,415
{\an1}-Kakashi, what are
you doing here?

226
00:12:13,448 --> 00:12:14,950
{\an1}-Your students told
me what happened.

227
00:12:14,983 --> 00:12:17,120
{\an1}And I got a little concerned.

228
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:19,922
{\an1}Dammit, he's got got backup.

229
00:12:19,956 --> 00:12:20,990
-So what?

230
00:12:21,024 --> 00:12:23,227
We'll get rid of
them with Fire Style.

231
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:25,329
Synergy Jutsu.

232
00:12:25,362 --> 00:12:26,096
-Go Iruka.

233
00:12:26,130 --> 00:12:26,597
ALL: Karura.

234
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,474
-Kakashi!

235
00:12:35,508 --> 00:12:38,677
{\an1}-That's one down.

236
00:12:38,711 --> 00:12:41,014
What?

237
00:12:41,048 --> 00:12:42,316
{\an1}-Lightning blade!

238
00:12:42,350 --> 00:12:44,318
[screaming]

239
00:12:49,358 --> 00:12:50,793
{\an1}-Thanks a lot Kakashi.

240
00:12:50,826 --> 00:12:52,261
{\an1}I don't know what
would've happened

241
00:12:52,294 --> 00:12:54,364
{\an1}if you hadn't shown
up when you did.

242
00:12:54,397 --> 00:12:56,699
{\an1}-I'm confident that you
would have kept Naruto safe,

243
00:12:56,733 --> 00:12:58,768
{\an1}even if I hadn't been here.

244
00:12:58,802 --> 00:13:01,238
{\an1}-Mm, you gave me good advice.

245
00:13:01,272 --> 00:13:03,174
{\an1}I think I understand it now.

246
00:13:03,207 --> 00:13:04,909
-Hmm?

247
00:13:04,942 --> 00:13:06,278
-You were right.

248
00:13:06,311 --> 00:13:10,216
{\an1}I should have tried to be honest
with him right from the start.

249
00:13:10,249 --> 00:13:12,285
{\an1}I probably tried to
turn my back on him

250
00:13:12,318 --> 00:13:13,686
so I could avoid
my own feelings.

251
00:13:13,719 --> 00:13:17,558
{\an1}But I think that I can
finally face him now.

252
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:20,694
{\an1}-I see, that's good.

253
00:13:20,727 --> 00:13:21,196
-Thanks.

254
00:13:29,605 --> 00:13:33,577
{\an1}-This map details The Leaf
Village's patrol network.

255
00:13:33,609 --> 00:13:36,613
{\an1}So this is what they
were trying to get then?

256
00:13:36,646 --> 00:13:37,814
-Yes.

257
00:13:37,849 --> 00:13:39,117
-Excellent work.

258
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:42,019
{\an1}I'll have the patrol unit
reexamine their village sentry

259
00:13:42,053 --> 00:13:43,856
{\an1}patterns right away.

260
00:13:43,889 --> 00:13:45,492
-Please do.

261
00:13:45,525 --> 00:13:46,992
{\an1}-It was coincidence.

262
00:13:47,025 --> 00:13:49,262
But even so, it
appears that Naruto

263
00:13:49,295 --> 00:13:51,197
{\an1}has saved the entire village.

264
00:13:51,231 --> 00:13:52,966
{\an1}You may leave now.

265
00:13:52,999 --> 00:13:53,601
-Yes sir.

266
00:13:58,406 --> 00:13:59,707
-What is it?

267
00:13:59,741 --> 00:14:03,879
-Lord Hokage, I
just-- I just wanted

268
00:14:03,912 --> 00:14:07,417
{\an1}to thank you for placing
me in charge of Naruto sir.

269
00:14:07,451 --> 00:14:08,684
-Hmm?

270
00:14:08,718 --> 00:14:10,587
-It's because of
that assignment I

271
00:14:10,621 --> 00:14:12,689
remembered why I
wanted to do this,

272
00:14:12,723 --> 00:14:15,160
{\an1}why I wanted to be a teacher.

273
00:14:15,193 --> 00:14:16,528
It all started
with something you

274
00:14:16,561 --> 00:14:19,598
{\an1}told me, Lord Hokage,
a long, long time ago.

275
00:14:24,538 --> 00:14:26,540
[sobbing]

276
00:14:26,573 --> 00:14:30,111
{\an1}-It's hard to believe
it's been a year already.

277
00:14:30,144 --> 00:14:31,379
{\an1}You're very brave.

278
00:14:31,412 --> 00:14:34,215
{\an1}It's hard to do that, to
hide sadness behind laughter.

279
00:14:38,253 --> 00:14:39,922
Your instructors
have been telling me

280
00:14:39,955 --> 00:14:42,358
{\an1}that you're among the most
playful of all their students

281
00:14:42,392 --> 00:14:44,194
and that you're
always so full of fun.

282
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:49,767
-You're wrong!

283
00:14:49,800 --> 00:14:52,404
{\an1}I'm not sad about anything!

284
00:14:52,437 --> 00:14:57,243
{\an1}It's a noble thing to die in
the line of duty, isn't it?

285
00:14:57,276 --> 00:15:00,880
{\an1}My parents both gave their
lives to protect this place

286
00:15:00,913 --> 00:15:02,583
{\an1}from the fox demon!

287
00:15:02,616 --> 00:15:03,550
They're heroes!

288
00:15:03,584 --> 00:15:05,420
{\an1}I'm the son of those
revered heroes.

289
00:15:05,453 --> 00:15:09,157
{\an1}I'm not even sad because they
went and left me all alone.

290
00:15:09,190 --> 00:15:10,526
If I cry it's
because I'm proud--

291
00:15:10,559 --> 00:15:12,827
{\an1}-It's all right Iruka.

292
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:14,964
{\an1}I know that somewhere
inside of you

293
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:19,903
{\an1}there's a boy curled
up in a ball of pain.

294
00:15:19,936 --> 00:15:24,342
{\an1}But remember this,
you are not alone.

295
00:15:24,375 --> 00:15:27,111
{\an1}Inside every ninja
of The Hidden Leaf,

296
00:15:27,144 --> 00:15:28,779
{\an1}there burns the Will of Fire.

297
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:33,319
{\an1}-The Will of Fire?

298
00:15:33,353 --> 00:15:37,757
{\an1}-It's what gives us the
strength to defend our village.

299
00:15:37,790 --> 00:15:41,696
{\an1}It's the unbreakable bond
the ties us all together.

300
00:15:41,730 --> 00:15:44,332
{\an1}It's what makes us a family.

301
00:15:44,366 --> 00:15:48,937
{\an1}(LAUGHING) I wonder, do you
have it yet, young as you are?

302
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:55,579
-I think so.

303
00:16:00,685 --> 00:16:02,587
{\an1}I wish to pass on
the Will of Fire

304
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:08,827
{\an1}to the children of the future,
to children like Naruto.

305
00:16:08,861 --> 00:16:11,331
-Huh.

306
00:16:11,364 --> 00:16:13,967
{\an1}-Aw, come on Sensei,
give me a break.

307
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,835
{\an1}How could you have
lost that kunai?

308
00:16:15,869 --> 00:16:16,337
-You

309
00:16:16,370 --> 00:16:17,738
-Idiot

310
00:16:17,772 --> 00:16:20,575
-Ah!

311
00:16:20,609 --> 00:16:21,876
{\an1}-Are you kidding?

312
00:16:21,909 --> 00:16:25,380
{\an1}You almost lost your life
today because of that thing.

313
00:16:25,415 --> 00:16:28,051
{\an1}-Yeah, that's true, but--

314
00:16:28,084 --> 00:16:30,887
{\an1}-Huh, you seem quiet today.

315
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:32,723
{\an1}-That's because this
is the first time

316
00:16:32,756 --> 00:16:34,825
{\an1}that you've actually
yelled at me Sensei.

317
00:16:34,858 --> 00:16:36,728
{\an1}I'm just surprised.

318
00:16:36,761 --> 00:16:38,330
-Yelled at you?

319
00:16:38,363 --> 00:16:39,765
I guess I did.

320
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:42,000
That's because I
decided I'm going

321
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:44,837
{\an1}to be more honest and
upfront with you from now on.

322
00:16:44,870 --> 00:16:48,408
{\an1}Starting tomorrow, I'm going
to be harder on you than ever.

323
00:16:48,442 --> 00:16:49,810
-Huh?

324
00:16:49,843 --> 00:16:53,880
{\an1}If that's how it's going to be
I'm never going back to school.

325
00:16:53,914 --> 00:16:58,019
{\an1}-Naruto, do you have
the Will of Fire in You

326
00:16:58,052 --> 00:17:00,289
{\an1}-The Will of Fire, what is that?

327
00:17:00,322 --> 00:17:02,726
It's the strong
will to do whatever

328
00:17:02,759 --> 00:17:05,595
{\an1}it takes to protect the
Leaf Village no matter what.

329
00:17:05,628 --> 00:17:07,732
{\an1}If you have it, then
you can become as strong

330
00:17:07,765 --> 00:17:08,965
{\an1}as the Lord Hokage.

331
00:17:08,998 --> 00:17:09,933
-The Hokage?

332
00:17:09,966 --> 00:17:12,303
Is he really as
strong as they say?

333
00:17:12,336 --> 00:17:13,572
-He is.

334
00:17:13,605 --> 00:17:16,007
{\an1}But he's got more
than just strength.

335
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:19,345
{\an1}Lord Hokage has the respect
of everyone in the village

336
00:17:19,379 --> 00:17:21,147
{\an1}because he's a great leader.

337
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:24,050
{\an1}The fourth Hokage was a hero
who protected the village

338
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:25,319
{\an1}from the Nine-tailed fox.

339
00:17:25,352 --> 00:17:28,188
-A hero?

340
00:17:28,222 --> 00:17:29,624
That's it then.

341
00:17:29,657 --> 00:17:33,595
{\an1}I'm going to be an even stronger
Hokage than the fourth Hokage.

342
00:17:33,629 --> 00:17:35,731
{\an1}And then everyone
in the village will

343
00:17:35,765 --> 00:17:37,700
{\an1}have to acknowledge
how great I am.

344
00:17:37,733 --> 00:17:38,200
-Hmm.

345
00:17:43,907 --> 00:17:47,311
{\an1}-Well, my guess is, that by the
time you're about this tall,

346
00:17:47,345 --> 00:17:48,946
{\an1}you might be able
to become Hokage.

347
00:17:48,980 --> 00:17:54,219
{\an1}-OK, then I'll work just as
hard I can until that day comes.

348
00:17:57,724 --> 00:18:07,769
{\an1}-Naruto-- I believe you really
might become Hokage one day.

349
00:18:07,769 --> 00:18:12,974
{\an1}-Naruto-- I believe you really
might become Hokage one day.

350
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:17,146
{\an1}-Iruka Sensei, could you
give us a hand with this?

351
00:18:17,180 --> 00:18:18,315
{\an1}-Yeah, sure thing.

352
00:18:18,348 --> 00:18:19,149
I'm on my way.

353
00:18:27,992 --> 00:18:28,894
[sighs]

354
00:18:33,867 --> 00:18:36,002
{\an1}-Where had Suigetsu gone?

355
00:18:36,036 --> 00:18:37,237
-Suigetsu?

356
00:18:37,270 --> 00:18:39,507
{\an1}huh, he went out two
or three days ago

357
00:18:39,540 --> 00:18:41,209
{\an1}and hasn't bothered
to come back yet.

358
00:18:41,242 --> 00:18:44,713
{\an1}To tell you the truth, I don't
care if he ever comes back.

359
00:18:44,746 --> 00:18:48,016
{\an1}-I heard that, you know?

360
00:18:48,050 --> 00:18:50,353
{\an1}-The executioner's blade?

361
00:18:50,386 --> 00:18:52,957
{\an1}You went all the way back
to get that old thing?

362
00:18:52,989 --> 00:18:54,725
{\an1}-Well, you left it behind.

363
00:18:54,758 --> 00:18:57,228
{\an1}It was a real pain to get back.

364
00:18:57,261 --> 00:19:00,030
{\an1}-I had better things to do
than worry about your stuff

365
00:19:00,064 --> 00:19:01,666
{\an1}when we fought the
Eight-tails, OK?

366
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,936
{\an1}-Yeah, well, I carried the
two of you out of there

367
00:19:03,970 --> 00:19:05,170
{\an1}when you were dying.

368
00:19:05,203 --> 00:19:07,072
{\an1}So quit fighting.

369
00:19:07,106 --> 00:19:08,876
{\an1}-Oh, patronize me why don't ya?

370
00:19:08,909 --> 00:19:12,246
{\an1}-Yeah, whatever, I'm just
glad I have this baby back

371
00:19:12,279 --> 00:19:12,880
{\an1}where it belongs.

372
00:19:16,417 --> 00:19:18,152
{\an1}I'm incomplete without it.

373
00:19:18,186 --> 00:19:20,723
-Now that all of
us are here, it's

374
00:19:20,756 --> 00:19:22,324
{\an1}time to get ready to leave.

375
00:19:22,358 --> 00:19:23,459
-Huh?

376
00:19:23,492 --> 00:19:25,060
{\an1}You're all healed up?

377
00:19:25,094 --> 00:19:27,364
-Yeah.

378
00:19:27,397 --> 00:19:29,399
{\an1}-We're heading to The
Hidden Leaf Village.

379
00:19:37,442 --> 00:19:39,311
-And that's it.

380
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:42,015
{\an1}-I never imagined Pain
would be defeated.

381
00:19:42,047 --> 00:19:44,617
{\an1}-This is most unexpected.

382
00:19:44,651 --> 00:19:47,353
{\an1}-And Konan's not coming
back here either.

383
00:19:47,387 --> 00:19:48,455
{\an1}-What should we do?

384
00:19:48,489 --> 00:19:51,325
{\an1}So many of our members are gone.

385
00:19:51,358 --> 00:19:53,227
{\an1}-We need more palms
to synchronize

386
00:19:53,260 --> 00:19:56,665
{\an1}with the Gedo statute again.

387
00:19:56,698 --> 00:20:01,404
{\an1}Kisame, you go track
down the Eight-tails.

388
00:20:01,437 --> 00:20:03,006
-What about you?

389
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:05,174
{\an1}-I have some other
business to attend to.

390
00:20:17,991 --> 00:20:22,362
{\an1}-This is much worse
than I imagined.

391
00:20:22,395 --> 00:20:24,799
-You're late.

392
00:20:24,832 --> 00:20:26,166
{\an1}-Did Naruto do all this?

393
00:20:26,199 --> 00:20:29,570
{\an1}-No, it was all Pain's doing.

394
00:20:29,604 --> 00:20:30,072
-What?

395
00:20:30,104 --> 00:20:30,906
Pain?

396
00:20:30,939 --> 00:20:33,542
{\an1}-Yeah, but Naruto handled it.

397
00:20:33,575 --> 00:20:35,612
{\an1}He defeated pain by himself.

398
00:20:35,645 --> 00:20:36,512
-He did?

399
00:20:36,546 --> 00:20:38,281
{\an1}What about the Nine-tails?

400
00:20:38,314 --> 00:20:41,785
{\an1}-Naruto was able to
control it all on his own.

401
00:20:41,819 --> 00:20:42,786
[sighs]

402
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:44,254
{\an1}-Well, that's good news.

403
00:20:44,288 --> 00:20:47,224
{\an1}Oh, wait-- Naruto controlled
the Nine-tails on his own?

404
00:20:47,257 --> 00:20:49,561
{\an1}-There's no time to
worry about that now.

405
00:20:49,594 --> 00:20:51,931
{\an1}We have to focus on
rebuilding the village.

406
00:20:51,964 --> 00:20:53,933
{\an1}It's going to be hard work.

407
00:20:53,966 --> 00:20:57,269
{\an1}Yamato, we're going to need
all the help you can give us.

408
00:20:57,303 --> 00:21:00,108
-Right.

409
00:21:00,140 --> 00:21:01,643
-What is it?

410
00:21:01,676 --> 00:21:03,578
-An emergency
council's been called.

411
00:21:03,611 --> 00:21:05,814
As Jounin squad
leader, you're required

412
00:21:05,848 --> 00:21:07,516
{\an1}to be there, Lord Shikaku.

413
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,220
-Already?

414
00:21:11,253 --> 00:21:12,689
All right then.

415
00:21:23,869 --> 00:21:25,771
[theme music]

416
00:22:56,011 --> 00:22:58,948
{\an1}KAKASHI HATAKE: So this
is where Naruto lives.

417
00:22:58,982 --> 00:23:00,083
-He's a fool.

418
00:23:00,116 --> 00:23:02,552
{\an1}But it would be best if
you looked after him.

419
00:23:02,585 --> 00:23:03,821
-Sure.

420
00:23:03,854 --> 00:23:06,824
{\an1}-He'll be on your team,
along with Sakura and Sasuke.

421
00:23:06,857 --> 00:23:08,325
{\an1}KAKASHI HATAKE: I'm
not naive enough

422
00:23:08,359 --> 00:23:11,296
{\an1}to go easy on them because
of personal feelings.

423
00:23:11,329 --> 00:23:13,065
{\an1}-I wish you the best of luck.

424
00:23:13,099 --> 00:23:14,901
{\an1}You're Going to need it.

